BOOK ONE

XXXVI 11

To my Cupbearer

HIS Persian luxury, my boy, l hate, Nor care for chaplets bound with linden bast: lnquire not in what covent, blooming late, The rosae linger last.

To beautify plain myrtle never think, 1 pray thee: meet are myrtlae that we twine For thee who servaet and for me who drink Beneath my close-pleached vine.
